The paper discusses the use of resistive crossbars for accelerating Deep Neural Networks (DNNs), which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The paper also addresses the issue of accuracy degradation in DNNs due to line-resistance induced errors, which is a topic of interest in the fields of Architecture (cs.AR), Neural Networks (cs.NE), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms for optimizing the crossbar re-arrangement, which involves the use of memristive devices, falling under the category of Electronic Devices and Materials (cs.EM).
